pageContext.claim: “We have thousands of people outside wanting to get into and they can't, because you people got here first. But so here’s your headline tomorrow: ‘Protestors Disturb the Rally.’ One protester, a very weak voice.”
pageContext.analysis: Doubly false. Nearly 100 protesters were outside this Trump rally in Milwaukee -- not one, as Trump absurdly claimed -- and the overflow crowd did not number in the thousands. "The crowd that couldn't get into the rally and stuck around in the overflow area outside had dwindled to a few hundred people by 8 p.m.," according to the Milwaukee Journal-Sentinel.
